# Run Tests After Code Changes

Whenever you modify code in this project, run the relevant tests before considering the task complete.

- **After changing anything under `auth/`** or auth-related routes in `app.py`: run  
  `pytest tests/ -v`
- **After changing agent code** (`agent/`, parser/scheduler/sender): run any existing tests that cover that code; if none exist, run at least  
  `pytest tests/ -v`  
  to ensure auth and app still work.
- **After changing `app.py`** (routes, middleware): run  
  `pytest tests/ -v`

Prefer running the full test suite (`pytest tests/ -v`) so nothing is missed. Fix or adjust tests if your changes intentionally change behavior.
